<L>__{interior osborne house, stables day}
<A>__{a few minutes later, brown is in the process of stabling his horse. suddenly he turns. victoria is standing at the far end of the stable with her entourage.}
<C>__{victoria}
<D>__{mr brown.}
<C>__{brown}
<D>__{yes, ma'am.}
<C>__{victoria}
<D>__{you have been told repeatedly not to stand in the courtyard unless requested to do so.}
<C>__{brown}
<D>__{yes, ma'am.}
<C>__{victoria}
<D>__{then why do you persist in doing it?}
<C>__{brown}
<D>__{because i think her majesty is wrong. if ever there was a poor soul who needed fresh air, it is her.}
<A>__{a beat.}
<C>__{victoria}
<D>__{the queen will ride out if and when she chooses.}
<C>__{brown}
<D>__{and i intend to be there when she's ready.}
<A>__{silence. the two of them stare at each other.}
